This paper discusses the application of ensemble methods in Reinforcement Learning, which falls under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also draws parallels from committee voting rules in Social Choice Theory, which falls under the category of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) and Game Theory (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper discusses the aggregation of actions, which can be related to Data Structures (cs.DS).
